inn1.comm: starts off with a full and wide swinging delivery, Rohit chased it and sliced it in the air towards third man
another full and swinging delivery, would have been a testing one for a right-hander, but it's a comfortable wide against a left-hander
now he corrects the line and Dhawan pounces on that with a crunching cover drive, but Australia have smartly kept a man at deep cover
length delivery on the middle and leg line, the batsman defends it towards midwicket
he keeps it on the leg stump line and a touch short of length, the batsman defends it solidly to the leg side
he keeps it just short of length and around the middle and leg line, the batsman defends it to the off side this time
angled across the left-hander, Dhawan presses forward but then lets it go through
keeps it full and on off stump, 136.6 kph, some shape on it as well, Rohit comes forward and defends it towards mid-on
again, pushes it fuller on off stump line, the batsman doesn't come fully forward as he defends it back to the bowler
he pushes it too far down this time, it goes wide down the leg side
he bowls another full delivery, this one shapes in a touch, Rohit defends it towards midwicket off the front foot
he decides to attack this delivery and lofts it over mid-on - who is standing closer - , it just clears the fielder and runs away quickly to the boundary
the bowler shortens the length a touch and pushes this one a touch outside off this time, the batsman lets it go
bowls it from wide of the crease and on a length outside off, gets it to straighten but Rohit wasn't playing a shot at that
he bowls a fuller outswinging delivery again, and like the last over, it swings too far down the leg side, Haddin only gets a hand to it
pushes it wider outside off this time, but Dhawan, instead of going towards cover, goes straight down the ground. Mid-off was a touch wider this time.
this is Dhawan timing now! He gets a half-volley on the pads and he times it between the midwicket and mid-on fielder, no one moved..
again swinging on his pads and that's invitation for trouble by McKay, Dhawan flicks it through square leg for third boundary in a row
now he charges down the pitch and pushes the length delivery on off to deep cover for a single
he gets a full delivery on off stump, Rohit comes forward and defends it towards cover
this has been delicately cut past the lone slip fielder and the ball looks headed to the boundary, but the third man fielder comes in quickly, swoops the ball in and fires it back quickly
he bowls short of length wide outside off, 141 kph, the batsman leaves it alone
he comes forward and pushes the full delivery to extra cover
bowls back of length delivery on the stumps, Rohit nudges it towards mid-on and calls early for a quick single

he gets a massive top-edge as he attempts a pull, the ball goes very high towards deep backward square leg, the fielder from fine leg charges in but cannot make it in time before the ball drops. Dhawan was cramped for room at that one, it was 140 kph
defends this one solidly to the bowler off the back foot
length delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and opens the face to push it to backward point
starts off from round the wicket, he bowls a short and wide delivery on off, but the batsman is not able to time his cut, chops it on behind the stumps
he delivers a short of length delivery on the body, Rohit defends it towards point
he plays a check drive this time and lobs it towards mid-off, everyone looks at the ball, which drops well short of the fielder. Faulkner as his hands on his head
he likes the angle this time and cuts the short of length delivery behind point for a boundary
this time he bowls it straight on the stumps, Rohit defends it back to the bowler
bowls it across the right-hander who lets it go through
oh this fuller delivery on the middle stump is beautifully driven down the ground, but the bowler does very well to stop that one while falling on his follow through
back of length delivery on the pads, that is asking for trouble, Dhawan swats it behind square leg for yet another boundary
this one is straighter and on the off and middle line, Dhawan defends it towards cover
how does he pick these gaps with such precision! It was a fullish delivery on off, Dhawan comes forward and times it through extra cover with ease
this time his bat again makes that lovely sound as he slaps the fuller delivery towards point, but it's hit straight to the fielder
another full delivery on the pads and another super on-drive through midwicket by Dhawan, he is doing it with ease at the moment
he bowls it short and he bowls it very wide outside off, the keeper takes it in front of the first slip fielder
better delivery this time, it's straight and on the stumps, slightly short of length and the batman defends it off the back foot
he gets room as the ball is angled and it's short as well, the batsman without any trouble cuts it through point for another boundary.. 50 is up
first time a batsman is beaten, it was a short of length delivery outside off, seems like it's coming in, but straightens a touch to beat the bat
slightly slower this time by Faulkner and on a length, the batsman defends it to point
this is a good line by Faulkner, he bowls short of length on off and gets it to straighten, Rohit is squared up a touch but manages to defend it to point
there is some room on this one, the batsman nudges it to third man to keep the strike
keeps it in the channel outside off, the batsman lets it go
another good delivery outside off, 131 kph, bounces a touch extra and Rohit just pulls his bat in in the nick of time
another length delivery outside off, the batsman defends it to point off the back foot
another one beats the bat as Watson pushes it fuller, Rohit wanted to drive, but his front foot was not moving in the line of the ball, plays inside the line
length delivery on off stump, the batsman whips it to backward square leg for a single
back of length delivery just outside off, Dhawan stays on the back foot and defends it towards point
he keeps it tight around off stump, the batsman gets up on his toes to defend it towards point
he comes forward the a length delivery and punches it on the up to widish mid-off
bowls this short and angling into the body, 132 kph, Rohit wanted to smash it out of the ground with a pull shot, but gets hit on the thigh pad
another aerial push by Rohit as he comes forward to the length delivery and tries to push it towards midwicket, but it lobs towards mid-on and drops safely
he comes forwards to the length ball and opens the face a touch to push it in the gap at cover for a couple
and this one is lobbed too, lobbed all the way to the stands over long-off, it's just a beautiful aerial cover drive and the timing gives it all the distance
length delivery on the pads, 133 kph, Dhawan wanted to work it to the leg side, but inside edges it on to his pads
another delivery on a tight line, the batsman comes forward and punches it to mid-off
he bowls this short one on the body and Dhawan wanted to play the pull, but it doesn't bounce as much as he thought it would and he gets a punch on the belly..
he comes forward and pushes it to deep cover with ease for a single
they steal an extra as the ball drops to the leg side after hitting the pads. Rohit was looking to flick it, but had missed it
length delivery on the pads and Dhawan flicks it fine on the leg side, Faulkner was at deep backward square leg and charges in to cut the boundary
and he strays only a touch to the leg side with this short of length delivery, the ball hits the thigh pad and rolls down to the fine leg boundary. Umpire gives it to the batsman
length delivery outside off, the batsman cuts it hard to third man for a single
no room in this back of length delivery, but Dhawan waits for it and opens the face of the bat very late to run it down to third man
length delivery in the channel outside off, the batsman pushes it to cover point
length delivery on the stumps, Rohit stays in the crease and clips it to deep square leg for a single
back of length and on the pads, easily flicked fine to the fielder in deep for a single
back of length delivery on off, the batsman pushes it to cover and thinks of a single, but Bailey picks it up and throws down the stumps in one action, then he smiles at the batsman
he charges down the pitch, but Watson shortens his length to surprise Dhawan, who gets out of the way in time
length delivery on on the pads, the batsman pushes it softly towards midwicket for a single
an accurate delivery on off stump and the batsman comes forward dabs it to midwicket for a single
short delivery on the body and Dhawan goes for a pull, he is not entirely in control of that shot, but ends up finding the boundary fine on the leg side
length delivery on the middle and leg line, Dhawan clips it with soft hands towards deep midwicket for a single
tossed up delivery on off, easily punched to wide long on for a single
pushes through on off, the batsman dabs it to the cover and calls for a quick single
he pulls out that flashy sweep shot, Maxwell dives to his right at square leg to prevent a certain boundary

oh there was a chance of a run out there! the batsman dabbed it to point and took off, but Watson was quick and sends the ball back, only that the throw was not accurate.. Dhawan would have been in trouble there
he charges down the pitch, but Doherty fires it short, it's punched back to the bowler
he comes forward and dabs it to the left of point fielder for a single
the batsman drives the length delivery on the up towards cover where Finch misfields, just fails to get down in time and the ball runs all the way to the boundary
back of length and on off stump, the batsman comes forward and defends it towards cover
bowls a shorter delivery on the body, Dhawan pulls it down to fine leg for a single
back of length delivery on the off side, Rohit stands up tall on his toes and guides it down to third man
he targets the pads, but he pushes it too far down the leg side
length delivery on off and middle, the batsman drives it to mid-on
another good delivery on off, the batsman pushes it to cover for a quick single
pushes it through on the middle stump, the batsman goes back and punches it straight down to long on
he comes forward and drives the fuller delivery to long off for a single
goes on the back foot to punch the quicker delivery to deep cover to bring up yet another half-century.. The machine just doesn't know how to stop
he comes forward and drives the fuller delivery to long off for a single
stays on the back foot and tickles the quicker delivery on his pads to fine leg for a single
quicker delivery just outside off, the batsman drives it with an open face, beautifully hit towards deep backward point, but the fielder cuts it off
short and wide, Dhawan chases it and slashes on the off side. finch is chasing the ball in the deep but he doesn't dive on time and misses it. Brings up the 100 partnership
full on the stumps, Dhawan leans forward and defends
on length on off, Dhawan comes down and pushes to cover
slightly shorter on off, cut late to short third man
on the stumps, Dhawan blocks it
ends the over with another short and wide ball, Dhawan cuts it to deep backward point and Finch limps while running to cut it to two
fullish on off, driven sweetly to deep cover for two
full on the stumps, driven back to Doherty
length ball on leg, defends it to midwicket
comes down the track to flick a length ball to midwicket
on length outside off, driven to sweeper cover for one
full on off and middle, swept to deep fine leg
on length outside off, pushed towards point
fullish on middle and leg, Dhawan defends it on the leg side
full on off, defends it back to Maxwell
back of length on middle, Dhawan goes back and pushes it to long-on
full on off, defended by Rohit
on length on the pads, pushed towards short fine leg for a single
on length on off, pushed towards point
tossed up on off, Rohit drives it down to long-off
pitched up on off, Dhawan defends with soft hands for a quick single
on the stumps, driven back to Doherty who dives to stop the single
on length on middle, pushed towards cover for one

Dhawan's gone! Doherty has struck here. He's not been flighting the ball much and pitched this one around middle from round the wicket and the ball turned into the batsman after pitching. He played across the line and missed it, plumb he was!
on length around off, Rohit defends with soft hands
back of length outside off, Rohit cuts it hard to third man
on length outside off, Kohli leans forward and defends
length delivery outside off again, Kohli defends with his head down

Kohli is run out for a duck!! It was a touch fuller as Kohli drove it down towards mid-on and set off for the single. Rohit also started but said no a little too late and by then Kohli was a long way down. The fielder throws it to the keeper and bails are off with Kohli way out of his ground. Australia now have two big wickets in the bag
on length outside off, Raina defends it to point
full on middle and leg, driven down to long-off
length ball on off, pushed down to long-on
full delivery outside off, driven handsomely to deep cover
length ball around off, Raina comes down to defend it
on the pads, tucked behind square on the leg side
flighted outside off, Rohit drives it to sweeper cover off the front foot
on length on the stumps, pushed to mid-on
back of length on middle, Rohit stays back and defends towards mid-on for a quick single
full and outside off, Raina pokes and misses. That wasn't too far from the outside edge
touch shorter and Raina pokes again, no footwork from Raina and misses the outside edge again
bangs it in short outside off, Raina defends on his toes
another short one angled into the batsman from outside off, Raina keeps it down towards midwicket
on length on middle and leg, pushed to cover by Rohit
slightly flighted and full on middle, driven down easily by Rohit
full on middle and leg, driven down to long-on
length ball outside off, Rohit drives it to deep cover
on leg as it turned away after pitching, Raina tucked it to short fine leg for a quick single
flighted on length outside off, Rohit chips it over the infield to del cover for two
back of length outside off, cut to third man for one
back of length on off, defends it back to the bowler
touch fuller outside off, driven down to mid-off
coming into the batsman after pitching short and Rohit cuts it to third man off the back foot, that's the fifty for him, took 71 balls for that
length ball aimed towards off, Raina defends it back to the bowler
short ball to Raina around middle, he stays back to guide it to deep fine leg and keeps the strike
short ball outside off and nearly another run-out! Raina slashed it on off and there was a misfield at cover which made Raina come down for a single but Rohit said not straightaway
length ball outside off, Raina pushes it back
that's full outside off and Raina merely pushes it along the ground past mid-on and it goes all the way. Not much follow through in the shot, it was a gently push and the mid-on wasn't too straight
back of length outside off, cut late to third man
outside off, Rohit taps it with soft hands on off behind square for an easy single
back of length outside off, Raina turns it towards deep backward square leg and they take two by the time del fine leg gets there
on length around off, Rohit tucks it on leg after some turn
on length on middle, Raina comes down and drives it firmly to long-off
that's a biggie - it goes al the way. Maxwell pitched it up on off and Rohit danced down the ground to launch it over the long-on boundary. 96 meters from the pitch
length ball on the stumps, pushed to long-on for one
back of length on off, tucked to the leg side for one
full outside off, driven straight to cover
bouncer from round the wicket, Raina pulls it wide of deep fine leg for two
another short one, this time well outside off and Raina taps it with soft hands wide of the keeper fine for a four. No slip in place
on length outside off, pushed to cover
length ball outside off, runs it down to third man
full outside off, driven to point by Rohit
on length outside off, Rohit drives again, tho time to cover
flighted and on leg, Raina sweeps it on leg for one
another one goes all the way. Rohit is targeting the spinners. Tossed up on middle and Rohit drove it straight down the ground for a six
on length on the stumps, Rohit defends this time
another full ball, this time towards leg and Rohit leans forward, plays against the spin and sends it over wide long-on for another six
on the pads, works it to backward square leg
tucked away off the hips square of fine leg for two
pitched up on the stumps, defends it back to the bowler
full on off, pushed towards the left of the bowler
he's unleashed after the fifty! Full ball and he launched it wide of long-on for six more
take that! Length delivery on the leg stump, Rohit comes out for eh crease and blasts this over deep midwicket now. He's dealing only in sixes now
full outside off, driven to deep cover for one
flattish and short of length on off, works it to deep cover
on length on off, tucked to midwicket
short of length outside off, Raina cuts it late to deep third man

Doherty gets another left-hander lbw! Pitched it on length on middle, Raina put his right foot forward to defend and there's where the ball hit him, it would have hit the stumps and Raina is unhappy wit the decision for some reason
on length on leg, defends it to midwicket
on length outside off, Yuvraj piths his foot forward and leaves it
length ball well outside off again and Yuvraj lets it go
short of length just outside off, Rohit defends opening the face of the bat and it misses the outside edge by a whisker
short of length on off, Rohit taps it to point
length ball outside off, runs it down to third man
bangs it in short towards the batsman, who turns it to deep fine leg
on length towards off, pushed down to mid-off
outside off again, taped down to third man
on length on off, Rohit leans forward and defends
flatter on off, driven down straight to cover
slower and on length on leg, tapped on the leg side with soft hands
full on off, driven down to long-off for a single
full around off, Yuvraj sends it back towards the bowler
back of length on leg, Yuvraj tucks it to deep fine leg off the back foot
bangs it in short to Yuvraj, he ducks in time to avoid it
short ball again, this time Yuvraj pulls it handsomely to the deep midwicket area for two
another bouncer, shorter than the previous delivery and Yuvraj sways out of the line

short ball, Yuvraj pulls and a top edge has gone for six! He didn't connect it at all, it wasn't timed properly as there wasn't much room and it went high up in the air but all the way over the fine leg boundary
back of length ball, Yuvraj pulls it to del midwicket
short of length outside off, Rohit taps it late and fine past the keeper with soft hands for four
starts off with a back of length delivery on off, the batsman stays back and wrists it to point
another back of length delivery outside off, Yuvraj stays on the back foot and guides it down to third man
he fires it full on off and Rohit flicks it with the angle to deep midwicket
back of length delivery on off and middle and the batsman stays on the back foot to nudge it to midwicket for a single

oh this is unbelievable by Haddin and Yuvraj doesn't get any respite! It was a fuller length delivery widish outside off, Yuvraj goes for a loose drive without getting anywhere near the line, gets a thick edge that Haddin plucks off his left hand with a quick reflex dive .. Stunning catch. He turns and hurls the ball in the air
he walks across the stumps and easily tucks the length delivery from round the wicket to deep square leg to get off the mark
starts off with a short and flat one which Dhoni thumps to wide long on for only a single
bowls it really slow and on the stumps, the batsman flicks it straight to midwicket
slow, short and filthy delivery, but it's so slow that it messes with Sharma's attempted punch through off
this one is better, the batsman defends it to midwicket
fires in one at 101 kph, the batsman punches it down to long on
whoa! this one cuts Rohit in half and goes over the top of middle stump, the keeper and the bowler appeal for a caught behind, but doesn't look like it hit anything
back of length delivery on off, the batsman gets up on his toe to defend
again cramps the batsman for room with a back of length delivery, Rohit looks to chop it to third man, but manages to dab it to the right of the wicketkeeper
length delivery on the stumps, Rohit comes forward and pushes it to long on for a single
he gets a back of length delivery and punches it to cover in his own style
this is a good start from Faulkner, he keeps it just short of length and very straight from round the wicket, Dhoni has no space to nurdle it and he defends it back to the bowler
back of length delivery on off, the batsman gets up on his toes and punches it to long off for a single
length delivery on off, Dhoni shuffles across and punches it straight down the ground to long on
bowled on the pads and Rohit flicks it to deep midwicket for another single
length delivery on off and he has taken some pace off it too, the batsman defends it to cover
short deliver outside off, doesn't rise much but Dhoni comfortably pulls it to deep square leg for a single
he pushes the full delivery straight to midwicket as the crowd keeps buzzing
he tries to throw the bat on the length delivery on off targeting the cover area,  but he gets a thick outside edge to third man
he gets a full delivery and he drives it beautifully with a classical front foot pose, but he finds the man at cover
another tight delivery on off, Rohit pushes it to mid-off , still no single

length delivery and the batsman just chip it cover extra cover to  get to his second hundred of the series, Virat is up clapping for him with a big smile on his face, relief for Rohit too after running out his partner. He punches the air
but Faulkner is keeping it tight on off, the batsman can only push it to the bowler
no room to cut again, the batsman chops it to the keeper
length delivery on the middle stump line, Dhoni pushes it to midwicket
another length delivery on a tight line, the batsman punches it to cover, still no runs
another tight delivery, Dhoni pushes it to the left of cover and calls for a quick single. The Aussie bowlers are not giving anything away
back of length delivery on off, slightly slower too, the batsman guides it straight to point
well, he makes room and slaps the back of length delivery over cover and into the crowd, not much of a power shot, just a gentle little slap
he stays in the crease and pushes the length delivery down to long on
angles it in and the batsman pushes it straight to midwicket off the front foot
oh beautifully driven over the infield for a one-bounce four, gracefully done and there wasn't much wrong with the delivery
short delivery and it comes in to the batsman, Rohit was looking to cut it firmly, but the ball bounced extra and came into him, beats the outside edge
length delivery on off, the batsman comes forward and drives it to deep extra cover for a single
back of length delivery on the body, Dhoni gets cramped for room and dabs it to midwicket. Rohit charges from the other end and is sent back, but he gets hit on the back by the throw
length delivery on the stumps, Dhoni hops and works it to deep midwicket for a single
back of length delivery on the stumps, Dhoni walks out of the crease but there is no room, he pushes it to cover
oh this one is on the pads and with the short fine up, it was never a good idea. Dhoni gets some bat on that and it's enough to earn him quatro runs
length delivery on off, the bowler is not really giving any room, Dhoni pushes it straight to point
and another one, tight length delivery on off stump, Dhoni stays in the crease and pushes it to mid-off
he takes a couple of steps to dab it towards midwicket for a quick single and a shy at the stumps at non-striker's end allows an overthrow
length delivery on off, the batsman can only push it as far as cover
length delivery honing in on off, Rohit comes forward and caresses it to deep extra cover for a couple
another length delivery on off, this time the batsman punches it a bit harder, drives it on the up and the fielder at deep extra cover had no chance
back of length delivery on the middle stump, Rohit nudges it to midwicket for a single
another back of length delivery on the stumps, Dhoni moves across and clips it to fine leg

oh that has burst through Moises Henriques fingers and Rohit gets another six! It was short and Rohit pulled it flat and fast to deep square leg, Henriques was readying himself for a simple overhead catch, but it just goes through
he comes forward and drives it to mid-off for a single
back of length delivery on the stumps, the batsman dabs it to cover point for a single
he walks down the pitch and McKay shortens the length, the batsman inside edges on to his body but runs across to complete a single
he moves towards the leg side but McKay follows him and Rohit can only push it to midwicket
length delivery on off, Rohit waits and steers it fine on the off side, but the short third man intercepts it
Gayle would be proud of that! It was a back of length delivery on the hips and he picks it from there, swings his bat to send it way deep into the stands at deep square leg
a full toss, we haven't seen too many, but Rohit slices it straight to point and he is disappointed with that result
short of length delivery on the body, Dhoni swivels to pull it down to fine leg for a single
full delivery on off stump but Rohit flicks it to wide long on for a couple of runs with a wristy push
length delivery on off, the batsman looks to steer it to third man, but chops it down to the keeper
fuller delivery on off, Rohit easily pushes it to long on off the front foot
on the middle and leg line and Dhoni clips it in the gap at deep backward square leg for a couple
again, he clips it to fine leg from off stump for a single, he keeps the strike
a back of length delivery and Dhoni hops on his crease and whips it away to deep square leg
oye! full delivery on off stump, N C-N was looking for the block hole, but this is creamed through extra cover with some style
now he stays back and tucks it through midwicket for an easy single
short of length delivery and Dhoni takes full toss, slapping it with a powerful pull to the cow corner
another short ball and while the last one went to the cow corner, this one is pulled to deep backward square leg
he fires a quick yorker on off stump and Dhoni digs it out to cover for a single
oh that was a great attempt at deep midwicket by Maxwell, but he is not able to hold on, so goes down as a drop. Dhoni skipped out of the crease and flicked one powerfully to the fielder in the deep
slightly short of length and Rohit swings his bat, but gets an inside edge that runs through backward square leg for a boundary
he makes room and slaps it through point powerfully to bring up his 150 for the first time in his career
an appeal for caught behind, but the umpire is not interested. It was a wide and full delivery and Rohit wanted to send it over extra cover, he slips as well playing that shot, but he is safe
he gets a slower delivery on the pads and he nonchalantly flicks it over deep backward square leg for another six.
he bowls a yorker on off, but the batsman digs it out to cover for a quick single
and he hits the 11th - the most sixes by an Indian batsman in an innings - off a length delivery from Doherty, pulling it easily over deep midwicket
now Doherty fires it full outside off, but Rohit  slices it over backward point for another boundary, the hundred of the partnership comes up...
he flights this one and gets it to spin as well, the batsman gets a leading edge towards cover
skips out of the track and sends this full toss so deep over long on that people would stop thinking of Gayle, that is one massive monster hit
and now he sweeps, gets a top-edge that falls in the gap at fine leg. One bounce, two bounce and four...
comes out of the pitch and gets under the delivery to send it over long-on again, 26 runs off that over, Rohit is scoring for himself and Virat both here...
fuller length delivery on the pads, Dhoni swings his bat and gets an inside edge down to fine leg for yet another boundary

full and wide outside off, Dhoni bends down and just gets his bat under that, but the ball flies off the wood and over cover and clears the boundary.. .This is some flood and Australia don;t know what has hit them
it was a low full toss on the middle and Dhoni was aiming for the cow corner, but gets an inside edge on to his pads
and bowls a fullish length on the pads, the batsman flicks it to fine leg for a single
it's the chinook, it's the blackhawk and it has come loaded with ammunition, it has arrived, the length delivery has been helicoptered  out of the ground over long on ..
he gets a short ball and Dhoni throws his bat at that, his one hand comes off the bat too, but he gets enough to send it to the fine leg boundary

high full toss and this has been clubbed way way over long off, this is just unbelievable hitting and it's not an overstatement, he just takes his front foot out and slaps it over long off, deep into the stands
he gets a yorker, fine, but he squeezes it out through point for another boundary
another low full toss and he times it to extra cover where the fielder dives to get a hand, that was headed to the boundary too, but Doherty does well
from nowhere, he gets beaten by a full and wide delivery as he goes for the drive
low full toss on the pads and he flicks it easily to deep backward square leg for an easy single
the bowler comes round the wicket but that doesn't make any difference and Dhoni, choosing non-violence this time, pushes it through extra cover to bring his half-century

and six more over the covers! Rohit makes a double with a creamed drive off a length delivery, the second 100 has taken only 42 deliveries, such has been the ferocity of the assault.. He punches the air and gets a standing ovation

length delivery on the stumps and this one has been flicked over deep midwicket for yet another six, this is mental hitting, this is manic.. McKay is not even reacting anymore as he goes back to the mark

he comes round the wicket and bowls a full delivery on the pads and Rohit flicks it beautifully to fine leg where the fielder takes a forward diving catch. He gets a wink from McKay as he goes back, a wink of appreciation ... Australian fielders congratulate him as he trudges off the pitch..What an innings!!
he bowls it full outside off and Dhoni chooses violence this time, murders it back over bowlers head and McKay somehow gets out of the way
short delivery and Dhoni pulls it past the short fine leg fielder, he wasn't in control.. But what the hell.. runs nonetheless

full delivery on the pads and he flicks it to deep square leg and Dhoni calls for a couple, but there is none there.. He is out of the last ball to end the madness that has prevailed in the last few overs..

inn2.comm: starts with a four! Back of length out swinger outside off and Finch found the gap between cover and mid-off. Dhawan chased and dived but couldn't keep the ball inside
outside off on length, driven to cover
this one comes into Finch after pitching on length just outside off and he defends it towards point
length ball angled into the pads, tucked to deep fine leg
length ball into the stumps, pushed towards mid-on
on leg, worked to deep fine leg for one
slightly full at 140kph outside off, Hughes drives and an inside edge just misses the stumps one its way to fine leg

Shami strikes! Pitched it on length on middle and was heading towards the stumps as it hit Finch's pads in front of leg. The umpire's finger went up immediately but not sure if that would have hit the stumps for sure
length ball outside off, Haddin pushes to cover
slightly full outside off, defends it back to the bowler
another big appeal! Shami goes up again and this one probably did a bit too much after pitching outside off and hit him on the thigh as he was on his toes. Good decision form the umpire
on length outside off, Haddin prods it to point
it as going down leg for a wide and Hughes got bat on it to send it for four
length delivery headed for the stumps, defends it back to BK
drifting down leg again, worked to deep fine leg
shaping in from off on length, Haddin defends off the back foot
falls short of first slip! This one shaped away after pitching on length outside off, Haddin chased with a prod and got an outside edge to first slip
on length on leg, helped to deep fine leg and Hughes keeps the strike
full and outside off, driven firmly straight to cover
shaping away from Hughes from length outside off, he lets it go
bouncer from Shami and Hughes pulls it awkwardly to midwicket
on length on leg, works it to deep backward square leg for two quick runs
touch shorter and wide outside off, Hughes cuts and gets a bottom edge. It doesn't go anywhere
length delivery from middle heading to off, defended off the back foot back to Shami
outside off on length form BK, Haddin pokes it to point
coming into the batsman form back of length, defends on the leg side
on the stumps this time, Haddin defends it to midwicket
length ball outside off, tight lines this over from BK and Haddin defends again
back of length outside off, punched to cover off the back foot
slightly shorter on off, he pulls but can't connect properly
back of length on leg, worked off the hips to deep backward square leg
back of length outside off, Hughes drives off the back foot towards point and Yuvraj pounces to his left to stop it
on length outside off, defends towards mid-off with soft hands for a quick single
on length on off, defends it back to Shami
going straight towards off stump at 141kph, almost went through the defence as the batsman went to the back foot
angling into Haddin from length on middle, tries to work it on leg but gets hit on the pads
not much room outside off for Hughes, who defends it towards short cover
wider outside off and Hughes cuts it to deep backward point off the back foot
appeal for lbw and Haddin pulls a short ball, can't connect and it hit him in front of leg, was going down further
gets room outside off, it's on length and Haddin drives the outswinger over the covers for four
connects much better this time. It was angled into the pads, Haddin connected very well to send it flying over midwicket for another four
angled into the pads again form length, flicked to deep midwicket and Haddin keeps the strike
length ball on off at 141kph, inside edge hits the pads
142.3 kph, back of length ball outside off, it jabbed in sharply as Haddin tries to cut it but it went though him as Dhoni caught it
short one but he's not timed the pull properly as it goes over midwicket and they take two
140kph, just misses the off stump. Back of length ball coming in, Haddin makes room and doesn't connect and the ball doesn't connect with the stumps either as it went over them
short of length outside off, defends it to point
into the pads and he works it down the leg side with the wrists for a four to. Shami looks unhappy with that as he gave only two runs before that ball
short of length angling away around off, defends it back to the bowler
full on the pads, worked to deep backward square leg for two off the legs
full and outside off, driven down to mid-off
short of length around off and angling away, BK appeals for lbw as it hit the pad before bat but hit him outside the line
short of length outside off, pushed to backward point where Kohli stops the ball
length ball around off, Hughes defends off the back foot
low and slow full toss just outside off, driven with soft hands to mid-off after a bounce
length delivery outside off, driven handsomely throughout he covers for four. Excellent timing and nobody moved an inch
on length on the stumps, defends it to midwicket
going into the pads, Haddin flicks it over short fine leg with the wrists for a couple of bounces into the boundary. He's targeting Vinay Kumar to accelerate
length ball towards middle and leg, pushed to mid-on for one
short of length moving away after pitching, Hughes defends as he goes on his toes
short of length wide outside off, driven off the back foot to cover
outside off, Haddin makes room but manages only a bottom edge close to the pitch, gets a single
short of length outside leg, Hughes wants to pull it away but can't. Hits his pads for a dot ball
length ball outside leg, flicked off the pads through the midwicket fielder for four as there's nobody in the deep
back of length around off, Hughes comes down a bit and drives to sweeper cover
short of length, Haddin spots the length and stays back to pull it wide of Kohli at deep midwicket for four. 10 from the over
back of length outside off, worked to point off the back foot
slightly shorter and wider, Hughes cuts and Yuvraj dives to his left to stop it but hurts his arm a little but
Haddin makes room early, Vinay replies with a bouncer aimed towards him and he's pulled it just in time between deep fine leg and del square leg for a one-bounce four
on length this time heading towards leg, defends without much movement
length ball on middle, pushed to mid-on for a single
it's a no ball as the length delivery was defended on the off side
full on off, Hughes heaves and gets a leading edge in the air. Dhawan catches it at third man and they run one
strikes first ball! Pitched it full on the pads, Hughes turned it to midwicket with the wrists and it's taken easily by Yuvraj out there. Dhoni almost did a 180 split by the way
tossed up on off, pushed back and Ashwin dives to his right to stop it
tossed up on middle, works it to square leg with the turn
flighted on the stumps again, turned to midwicket
full on off, driven down to long-on for one
on length and flatter on middle, Haddin defends to midwicket off the back foot
back of length outside off, pushed back to the bowler
fuller outside off and swinging away, Bailey drives and misses it
bit of room outside off on length, pushed to point with soft hands for a quick single
on length outside off and shaping away Haddin pokes and misses the outside edge again
Haddin makes room, trying to break a few shackles, can't get the straight ball past mid-on
on length on the stumps, defends it back to the bowler
appeal for lbw as it pitched on off but was going down further when bailey shuffled and tried to work it on the leg side
this one zips across Bailey who wanted to drive it on off and beat his outside edge
full on the pads, swept to deep fine leg
on length on off, going across Haddin who wanted to defend but it just missed the outside edge
on length on middle and leg, worked to midwicket for a quick single
offspinner on off, pushed to midwicket on the last ball
length delivery on middle and leg, flicked in the air to deep midwicket off the pads

what a run-out this is, confusion all over for Australia! Bailey put the ball away to deep midwicket with a heave, they weren't sure about the second but went for it, Haddin tries hard to make it in time at the non-striker's end but Bailey isn't making his ground at the keeper's end, he's watching what's happening at the other end halfway through the pitch. Vinay collects the ball as Haddin dives and throws it to Dhoni, Bailey is well out of his crease caught napping
length ball on off, pushed on the off side
on length on off and middle, driven to mid-on
this one's on length just outside off, coming in a bat and an appeal for lbw as it hits the front pad, but hit him outside the line
back of length on off, pushed to mid-on for a single
tossed up delivery on off, the batsman defends it down the pitch
another loopy delivery but the room outside off allows the batsman to squeeze it through cover
flatter and quicker on off stump, the batsman defends it off the back foot
he bowls it flat and quick on off stump again, the batsman defends off the back foot

and Haddin's scratchy innings has come to an end! Dhoni isn't sure if the bails were flicked by the ball or by his hands! But the replays show that it took the top of the off bail. Another one goes down. That hit the top of off and ricocheted on to Dhoni's grill
he charges down the pitch and slaps it over mid-on for a couple of runs
he is not wasting any time, he charges down the pitch again and flat bats it over midwicket for another boundary
and Vinay Kumar gets the flavour of the day, this one is one amazing shot, he picked it up from the middle stump and sends it to the second tier at deep square leg
and skips down the track and launches this high and very very high in the night sky, for a second the fielder at long off thought he had a chance, but it descends into the crowd
tossed up and full, the batsman pushes it back to the bowler
quicker on off this time, the batsman defends it off the front foot
it's fuller on the pads and it's flicked to deep midwicket for a single
fires it full on off, Maxwell punches it back to the bowler
another one of those yorkers, Maxwell can only dig it out back to the bowler
and this is good bowling, another yorker by Ashwin, Maxwell forces it to long on for a single
he bowls a flat one and Maxwell is unstoppable, he stays on the back foot, leans back and smashes it over cow corner
tossed up outside off and Maxwell is going to target the leg side, slogs this one from off but it drops just short of the fielder at deep midwicket
he is more conventional, coming forward to push the full delivery to cover
plays this one with an open face and pushes it to deep cover
slightly slower and shorter, Maxwell waits for it and cuts it late past the lone slip fielder, this is very smart cricket
flatter and quicker outside off, the batsman wanted to blast it through covers, but gets an inside edge towards midwicket
he defends the first one to cover
tossed up delivery and Voges goes for a reverse paddle, but makes no connection as the ball turns down the leg side
he skips down the track and pushes it to midwicket for a quick single
tossed up on off, the batsman clears his front foot out and wanted to drive it through cover, but he misses and it beats the outside edge
now it's another tossed up one and the batsman gets down on the knee and sends it soaring behind square leg, goes into the stands again..
he bowls a quick yorker which Maxwell punches down to long on
he makes room as he charges down the pitch but misses the length delivery outside off, the record is not for the taking anymore

length delivery and he shows he is no less than his Mumbai teammate Rohit, drives it beautifully over extra cover to bring up the fastest fifty from an Aussie.. equals Simon O-Donnell's 18 ball effort
this one is a slower one and it beats the batsman just outside off, wasn't too far from either the bat or the off stump
bowls another fuller delivery at his normal pace and he scythes it over extra cover, but there is protection in the deep now
full delivery outside off, the batsman crunches a drive but Raina at cover swoops it by moving to his left

the leg stump has been taken out! Shami gets another one! It was a nothing shot really because Voges tried to whip it to the leg side while staying back to a length delivery, it skids in, hits his pads and then takes the stumps out. He played across the line and was probably surprised by the pace on that
he comes in and he his smacked for a massive hit over long on, length delivery, asking to be hit and it just ends up in Maxwell's arc

short delivery outside off and Maxwell in this mood was not going to leave it, he goes for the pull but doesn't get hold of it as the ball hits the top of the bat, it lobs towards Jadeja at deep midwicket who gobbles it up..
pushed to cover for a single
he plants his front foot out and punches the length delivery to extra cover, Dhawan rolls along the floor after he has stopped it, he mocks Watson's limp after that.. Watson doesnt find it funny
he punches the length delivery to mid-on for a single
back of length delivery on off, the batsman dabs it to cover for an easy single
length delivery outside off, he drives it on the up and punches it to cover
length delivery on off, Watson chops it to backward point for a single
back of length delivery on the stumps, the batsman stands tall and guides it to third man for a single
he stands tall and it doesn't matter if the ball was seaming after pitching on the length, he just picks it up with a straight bat over long on, over the advertising boards
add to that four more as he opens up the stance and drives it on the up through extra cover
fuller and slower delivery, Watson maintains his grim countenance and blasts this to long on, along the ground for a single
it's back of length on off and Watson just stands tall and gives it a jolly good whack over midwicket, the fielder was not too far, but it flew like a rocket
opens the stance and punches the length delivery to cover
he gets a length delivery to which he throws a wild swing, it just misses the off stump and the outside edge

now he connects and connects very very well, Watson is very serious, no smiles at all as he smashes it way way deep into the cow corner stands.. Looked like it was heading out of the ground at one stage
they keep coming, Vinay Kumar serves up a length delivery, Watson is not bothered about running, he smashes it over cow corner again, flatter this time but six nonetheless
make it a hat-trick! Dhawan may have just ticked Watson the wrong way here, he is just responding with the bat, this is deep in the second tier. Monster Monster Halloween hit this one.
he comes forward and pushes the tossed up delivery to cover
he pulls the length back and the batsman defends it to the bowler
he punches this one to long off for a single to give Watson the strike
quicker and fired on the leg stump, the batsman defends it towards cover
there were shouts of catch it, but the long off fielder can only see it sail very flat and very low, all the way towards the sight screen
tries to slog again, but inside edges it to midwicket
tossed up and full outside off, Faulkner swings it like a golf club, over the bowler's head
fired full on the pads, Faulkner flicks it straight to square leg
slog sweeps it from off stump to deep midwicket after taking his front leg out
he bowls a good yorker outside off, the batsman makes no connection as he tries to dig it out
flatter and quicker, he slaps it to long on, but decides against the single
full and on the middle and leg line, Watson blasts it back towards the bowler, who gets his left-hand to it, but it would have taken his hand along has he tried to put it flush in the way..
length delivery on the stumps, the batsman punches it back down the pitch, Shami gets a hand to it, but he parries it to long on
and this hit equals it! He moves the front leg out of the way and nonchalantly picks up the length delivery over long on, not just over long on, it's way way over long on
fires in a good yorker on off stump and we don't see them too often these days, the batsman digs it out back down the pitch
attempts another yorker on the middle stump, it's not really on the mark, but not bad either, the batsman punches it down to long on
length delivery outside off and the batsman doesn't care what pace it is or where it's coming from, he just slaps it over the non-striker's head, it goes over long-on, it was a slower delivery too
this is another good yorker, right on the middle stump and the batsman can only jam his bat at that
length delivery on off, the batsman pushes it to long on for a single. Watson hobbles to the other end

that is the end of Watson! Jadeja hurls some words at Watson's end after the wicket, totally unnecessary! Here is what happened! It was a shorter and flatter delivery on off, the batsman went for a cut, he chops it on to Dhoni's thigh and it ricochets to lob gently for the fielder at short third man. Watson wasn't sure what happened, but he has to go.
he comes forward and punches it to cover for  a single
fuller delivery, he comes forward and drives it to cover
floated wide outside off, the batsman tries to push it and gets beaten..
full delivery on off, the batsman pushes it to extra cover for a single
bowls the carrom ball on the pads, the batsman tucks it to behind square on the leg side
flatter delivery outside off, the batsman dabs it to point for a single
he cramps the batsman with room with one spinning in, the batsman pushes it to cover
Shami has dropped a dolly! This was slogged by the batsman and all Shami at deep midwicket had to do was to watch the ball and swallow it, but it just slips through his fingers
he pushes it to cover for a single
flatter and shorter on the pads, the batsman waits on the back foot and pulls it to fine leg

floated wide outside off, slower and loopy, the batsman didn't have much of an option but to go through with his shot, he aims for the sight screen, but he ends up in the big palms of Kohli at long on..
Faulkner will keep fighting, he gets under the full delivery and hammers it over long on
another drop, this time by Jadeja, as the batsman whacks it back at the bowler
he tries to punch the back of length delivery through off, but chops it to the keeper
now he is beaten as he bowls this one faster outside off
flatter and quicker of off, the batsman dabs it to point for a quick single
he tosses it up and Faulkner send it flying to the second tier over cow corner, this is outrageous hitting..
full and flighted on off stump, the batsman drives it firmly but straight to cover
he bowls it slower and wider outside off, the batsman had to wait and he slaps it hard, it just drop short of Yuvraj at extra cover
he eases the full delivery to long off for a single
bowls a carrom ball from over the wicket now, but it's short enough for the batsman to rock back and defend
a quicker one, 110 kph, the batsman defends it back to the bowler
short and wide, jabbed to point without footwork
wide again and this time's it's fuller as Faulkner smashes it through the covers for four
short of length and still very wide, Faulkner cuts it and it beats a wide short third man for another four. IT was quick at 93kph
full and closer to off, Faulkner lofts is down the ground over long-on, Rohit is running to his right and it goes through his hands for a six. Not an easy catch that one
outside off on length, cut to short third man
slower and wider, Faulkner waits for it and drives it to sweeper cover to complete his fifty
flighted low full toss outside leg, hits him on the back leg outside leg so not out and might have had an inside edge too
flatter and wider, way outside off and is called wide
flighted on the legs again, Faulkner turns this one to deep midwicket and they take two by the time Dhawan throws it back
gets room and he drives it away to the deep cover boundary by going over the infield for another boundary
flighted and full well outside off, another big wide
full on off, driven down to long-on for one
short of length outside off, goes back and pushes it to midwicket
straighter one at 88.5kph outside off, McKay cuts and misses
on length outside off, Faulkner gets down on one knee and heaves it to the wide long on boundary for six more
shorter and flatter, he charges down and slashes it past a diving cover for four more. He's raced to 65 off 41
flighted on the pads, defends off the back foot
short of length outside off, Faulkner stays inside and cuts is square this side, what's the result? Four!
fuller on off, forward defence goes on the leg side
flighted on off, McKay comes forward to defend
juicy full toss on off, he puts it away easily past long-on for a boundary served to him on a platter
gets a yorker this time, Faulkner blocks it back to Vinay
almost in the block hole outside off, driven to sweeper cover for one
on length on off, forward defence on the leg side
on length and into the batsman, Vinay appeals for lbw but there's an inside edge into the pads
another appeal for lbw as it was going into McKay and the umpire turns it down again. Going down leg and maybe an inside edge too
short and flat outside off, steered to deep point for one and a slip comes in
round the wicket, on length on off, defends it down to the bowler
fuller on off, steered past midwicket and he's off the mark
low full toss outside off, slashed back past the bowler to long-off
on length on middle, turned past midwicket for another single
short and flat outside off, worked wide of cover for one
Faulkner charges down, Vinay bangs in a bouncer and he's slapped it between long-on and deep midwicket for four, piercing the gap
four more! Full on off and it's driven down the ground beating mid-off to go all the way along the ground
attempted yorker is also a four! Low full toss on leg stump, flicked away off the pads, Jadeja ran to his right from deep midwicket and a dive can't save the boundary even though he reached there
fours are not enough, he smacks a six! Short ball on the stumps, its' n the zone for him and it's launched over Jadeja's head at deep midwicket for a six. He jumped but couldn't get there
full and outside off, driven handsomely through the covers and Kohli dives to his left from long-off to save two
short of length outside off, jabbed towards point for one to keep the strike
full on leg, pushed to cover softly and that's a hundred for Faulkner. It's his maiden and the fastest by an Australian. Big applause from the Bangalore crowd. What an effort from a No. 7 batsman
full on off, gets forward and pushes to cover
short and outside off, pushed past cover into the gap and Dhawan chases but can't get there. A four from McKay now
on length on off, defence off the back foot now
full on off, defends it back to the bowler
on length on off, gets forward and defends
in the block hole on off, pushed down to long-on for one
yorker on off, blocks it back to the bowler
short ball going down the leg side, McKay ducks but the umpire doesn't call it a wide
low full toss outside off, driven through the gap by McKay, he's joining Faulkner in this run-fest. Can Australia do it form here?
back of length aimed towards off, defends it off the back foot
full and outside off, driven nicely to cover
makes room, he bowls it wide down leg and it's pushed down to long-on
short and wide, it's another four and who hit it? It's not Faulkner, it's McKay who drive it past cover to send it all the way
flighted on off, blocks on the front foot
quicker one into the stumps, an inside edge onto the pads saves the batsman from bowled or lbw
full on middle, pushed back to the bowler

that's turn form Jadeja and Dhoni has appealed for a stumping. IT was on length outside off, the batsman drove but missed it and Dhoni took the bails off. Replays say its too close but his toe is just back in time
full and outside off, driven along the ground to deep cover
length ball outside off, McKay leans forward and defends
fuller outside off, driven down to give strike to Faulkner
and what happens when he's on strike? It's full again, and he sends it high up in the air, it looked like a mis-hit but it's gone all the way. SIX more
full and wide, driven to backward point this time
low full toss, pushed to deep extra cover with the full face of the bat, Faulkner keeps strike
almost yorked as James tries to flick it way, but he's hurt because the ball hit him full on the back foot
makes room, Jadeja bowls it down leg and he jabs it to cover
full toss outside leg, driven down to long-on for one
short of length outside off, defends it off the back foot to backward point
angled into the batsman, worked on the leg side for one
flighted on the pads, steered to deep midwicket and he keeps strike again
full on off, punched down the ground, it was going for four but Kohli dives to his right from long-off and saves three. Big cheer from the crowd
angled into the pads, it's going down leg as the appeal is turned down
coming in from outside off, worked to deep square leg for one
full on off, driven past the bowler to long-off for one
short of length around off, McKay defends it off the back foot
short of length outside off, defends it to cover
pitched it on leg, Faulkner slashes it to deep midwicket for one
full ont he stumps, pushed down to long-on
flat ball down leg, he made room to pull it but misses and goes between the batsman and the stumps
flat outside leg again, he connects but gets only a single to deep midwicket
full on off, McKay comes forward to defend

beat him! It was on length on off again, McKay came forward to defend but played the wrong line and it just beat the outside edge to hit the off stump. Jadeja breaks the big partnership of 115 on the last ball of his spell

full toss gets a wicket and it's all over! It was there to be put away, Faulkner hit it a long way in the air and Dhawan ran to his right from deep midwicket to take a diving catch to finish the match
